President Donald J. Trump has issued fact sheets on healthcare, specifically addressing the Opioid Crisis. The fact sheets highlight the progress made in tackling the driving forces of the crisis. The Administration has taken action to target both international and domestic suppliers of illicit opioids, aiming to cut off the supply. Additionally, efforts have been made to reduce demand for opioids within the United States. President Trump and his Administration are also working to assist individuals afflicted by drug addiction and help them recover.